Description: Fragment of a larger clay seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. On the rear on two sides each two coils of basketry, suggesting that the piece was attached between the lid and the wall of a basket. The front is flat and shows one flat impression of a complete scarab-like seal, very eroded. The seal shows three columns with Mn-kheper-R' in the middle, flanked with one Sw-feathers on each side.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), Temple, forecourt, top level
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 65)
